						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the temple of Bobbanāgi.</p>						

						<p>9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription can be assigned to 9th century A.D. on the basis of palaeography and other internal evidence.</p>						

						<p>Mentions Chāmōya, a pupil of Kālgarābharaṇa, who is described as an ornament of the Viśvakarma kula and the āchāryya of Jalpēśvara.</p>						

